node.text:
Pesto is one of the most popular sauces in the world. The original recipe calls for seven ingredients, no more, no less: basil, extra-virgin olive oil, pine nuts, Parmesan cheese, pecorino cheese, salt, and garlic. We traveled to Genoa, Italy, where pesto was invented, to meet Roberto Panizza, owner of Pesto Rossi and the restaurant Il Genovese, and find out what makes each of the seven ingredients so distinctly Genovese.

Featuring @clacly22 

#Pesto #PestoSauce #Italy #Genoa #RegionalEats #Food #Cooking #kitchen #Basil

node.title: How authentic pesto is made in Italy | Regional Eats

It’s harder to achieve a perfectly rich, moist chocolate cake than you might think. From too many eggs to not enough flour to switching oil for greek yogurt, Insider’s Lisa Paradise (@lisaparadise) made 18 different chocolate cakes, starting with Dominique Ansel's Go-To Chocolate Cake recipe as a base, to see how every single common baking mistake affects your final bake.

Every summer, Isabella, her mother, Dina, and her daughter, Federica, honor the family tradition and make tomato sauce in their garden. The process is a laborious one that takes several hours, from hand picking each tomato to adding basil leaves into jars one by one. This year, the family has turned more than 200 kilos of tomatoes into sauce.

The earliest record of cheddar anywhere is at Cheddar, in Somerset, in 1170. The land around this village has been at the heart of English cheesemaking since the 15th century. Today, as many Cheddar producers have upscaled and require more land, there is only one traditional cheesemaker in the village.

node.text:
If there were a competition for the most beautiful cheese, Cornish Yarg would claim the title. Each cheese is wrapped in wild stinging nettles, which are brushed on by hand one by one. With aging, the nettles form a natural rind around the cheese, giving it a fresh, creamy taste with hints of herbs, mushrooms, seaweed, and even lemon. So how did this recipe even come about? It was actually found randomly in a book about 400 years ago. We visited Lynher Dairies in the heart of Cornwall to find out more.

#cornishyarg #cheese #dairy #cornwall

node.title: How Cornish Yarg cheese is made | Regional Eats

node.text:
I ranked double cheeseburgers from McDonald's, Wendy's, Burger King, Shake Shack, and White Castle. White Castle blew me away with its small, cheap, and super-flavorful sliders. Shake Shack had the biggest burger, but it was also the most expensive.

Click the link in our bio to read more about the cheeseburgers.

(Credit: Erin McDowell/Insider; Deutschlandreform/Shutterstock; Sheila Fitzgerald/Shutterstock; Kiran's Captures/Shutterstock)
#Cheeseburgers #WhiteCastle #Mcdonalds

node.accessibility_caption: Photo showing the burgers with headline, "I tried double cheeseburgers from 5 fast-food chains and the cheapest burger blew me away"

Photo showing the burger with text, "This sandwich was definitely worth the price. It was less than what I usually pay for my morning coffee. It was also a little heavy for my liking. It filled me up a little more than I had anticipated before jumping into the rest of the taste test."

Photo showing the burger with text, "In fourth place was Wendy's double cheeseburger, which the chain calls a Double Stack. The toppings themselves were amazing. I thought the pickles were the most flavorful out of the burgers I tried, and I liked the use of an onion ring rather than diced onion."

Photo showing the burger with text, "The McDonald's double cheeseburger's bun held everything together and was a good size, but it was a little too soft and didn't have a lot of flavor on its own. But I enjoyed the amount of condiments and didn't find 
them overpowering."

Photo showing the burger with text, "Biting into the Shake Shack burger was a little overwhelming. The burger was huge, which was both an asset and a hindrance. I struggled to get through more than a few bites. However, despite being the most expensive burger, I definitely thought it was worth the price."

Photo showing the burger with text, "I was blown away by the cheeseburgers from White Castle. As the cheapest and smallest burgers, I was expecting them to be a little lackluster. However, I found that good things definitely come in small packages. The onions, condiments, and pickles were flavorful, but it was the beef that really sealed the win for White Castle."

Pesto is one of the most popular sauces in the world. The original recipe calls for seven ingredients, no more, no less: basil, extra-virgin olive oil, pine nuts, Parmesan cheese, pecorino cheese, salt, and garlic. We traveled to Genoa, Italy, where pesto was invented, to meet Roberto Panizza, owner of Pesto Rossi and the restaurant Il Genovese, and find out what makes each of the seven ingredients so distinctly Genovese.

Featuring @clacly22

node.text:
Insider’s Phil Rosen tried the garlic aioli chicken sandwich at Carla Cafe and found his new favorite lunch in LA.

The shop takes orders on its private Instagram, where it announces “sandwich drops” three times a week, offering the chicken sandwich or a “tuna chop.”

Click the link in our bio to read more about the secret sandwich spot.

(Credit: Phil Rosen/Insider)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo of a Carla Cafe sandwich with the headline, "I tried a secret LA sandwich shop that only takes orders via Instagram DM. It's my new favorite lunch spot."

Photo of a sandwich with the text, "In mere months, Carla Cafe owner Avi Ahdoot went from making himself a sandwich at home to selling 1,000 sandwiches per week out of a pop-up shop, all via private Instagram messages. It all started when his girlfriend posted this photo to Instagram and numerous people replied asking where to get one."

Photo of the outside of the club Bootsy Bellows with the text, "The Carla Cafe Instagram page is private. To order you have to request to follow the account. If the cafe accepts, you can message the account asking for a link to place an order. You show up at a hole in the wall outside the nightclub Bootsy Bellows for pickup."

Photo of a sandwich with the text, "The shop does a "sandwich drop" three days a week, usually with only one sandwich per drop — either Garlic Aioli Chicken or Tuna Chop, but on occasion they do a "duo drop." When I took my first bite, I knew it was the best sandwich I'd had in LA."

In the hot spring town of Laugarvatn, Iceland, the most pristine rye bread is baked in volcanic, muddy ground. Siggi Rafn Hilmarsson from Laugarvatn Fontana takes us through the making process step by step and welcomes us into his bakery, aka the hot springs of the lake in Laugarvatn. The sand by the lake can host from 10 to 15 tins of bread.

node.text:
Keke Palmer didn't seem to be a huge fan of the menu served at the Met Gala on Monday evening. 

The 28-year-old actress, who co-hosted Vogue's livestream coverage of fashion's biggest night alongside comedian Ilana Glazer, posted an Instagram story to her account on Monday evening of a sparse plate of the food that she was served at the event.

Captioning the photo of what looked like a variety of vegetables and some grains, Palmer wrote: "This why they don't show y'all the food," along with an emoji with the tongue sticking out, before adding that she was just joking in the following line.

Read the full story at the link in our bio.

(Credit: Getty Images, Keke Palmer/Instagram)

Taco Bell is testing a new 30-day Taco Lover’s Pass subscription, which runs for anywhere from $5 to $10 depending on location, and gets customers one free taco every day for 30 days.

Other restaurant chains have tested out similar subscriptions as a way to keep regular customers coming in and spending money in what some experts have dubbed the “subscription economy.”

(Credit: Taco Bell)

node.text:
When your workout is finished, you might think that the important work is behind you. But what you eat after your exercise can have a real impact on your fitness.

Insider spoke to John M. Martinez, MD, a sports medicine physician who has worked with the USA Triathlon team, about the best things to eat after a workout.

Click the link in our bio to read the full story.

(Credit: Getty Images; Hannah Lin/Spoon Unviersity; Yelp/Alex B.)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo of a plate of food with the headline, "5 healthy, satisfying foods to eat after a workout that will give your muscles the best chance to recover."

Photo of a poke rice roll with the text, "Fish and chicken are a great source of lean protein that can rebuild your muscles after an intense workout. Sushi, in particular, has a good balance of protein from the fish and carbs from the rice."

Photo of a quinoa salad with the text, "Quinoa is a complex whole grain that has the two post-workout essentials: carbohydrates and proteins. In addition, quinoa is gluten-free, so it's a good option for those who are gluten intolerant or who have celiac disease."

Photo of seasoned avocado slices on toast with the text, "Avocado is a good choice, especially for athletes on a low-carb or ketogenic diet. Its high fat content takes longer to digest keeping you feeling fuller for longer compared to, say, eating a bowl of plain white rice that's mostly simple carbs."

Photo of kale being tossed by hand with the text, "Dark leafy vegetables such as spinach and kale provide essential nutrients like calcium and iron, which can help you perform. Calcium helps with muscle repair and bone strength, while iron helps regulate metabolism and energy consumption."

Photo of a shake with the text, "Protein shakes are a quick and easy way to get protein post-workout. It's important to make sure that you're drinking a high-quality protein shake that isn't filled with sugar. High-quality protein shakes usually supply about 30 grams of protein."

Be it summer or winter, there is nothing that warms your heart more than a freshly baked croissant. But achieving these flaky, crunchy layers just can't be done overnight; it takes days of preparation and butter — lots of butter. We visit Frédéric Roy in his bakery in Nice, on the French Riviera, where he shows us how true artisanal croissants are made.
